From: Murray S. Kucherawy <msk@opendkim.org>
To: opendkim-announce@lists.opendkim.org, opendkim-users@lists.opendkim.org
Subject: OpenDKIM v2.4.2 released

The OpenDKIM project announces availability of OpenDKIM v2.4.2, now available
for download from SourceForge.

This is a minor bug fix release prior to beginning development work on the
v2.5.x line, which will contain new features.  Upgrading is not required
or urgent unless you're specifically interested in one of the changes
listed below.

The full RELEASE_NOTES for this version:

2.4.2		2011/08/05
	Don't apply BodyLengthDB when not signing.  Problem noted by
		Andreas Schulze.
	LIBOPENDKIM: Update for draft-kucherawy-dkim-atps-06.
	LIBOPENDKIM: Terminate the strings returned by dkim_sig_getsubstring()
		and dkim_sig_getidentity() whenever possible.  Suggested by
		Heikki Gruner.
	CONTRIB: Change "chkconfig" instruction in RHEL init script,
		and a minor tweak to the RPM spec file.  From Steve Jenkins.

Please use the mailing lists at http://lists.opendkim.org/ to report problems.
Bug reports and feature requests can be made through the project trackers,
which can be found via http://www.opendkim.org.

The OpenDKIM Project
